 that you can only ever loot them once. (Imagine not having to compete against a farmer for said haste sash.)<br>- Quests will be randomly generated and will not require the player to ask and properly spell specific words or phrases.  You'll just mouse-click on the key words to advance the conversation.<br>- Quest mobs will drop one item <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> per person</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in the group doing that particular quest. (Imagine a mob like Quillmane dropping a quest cloak every time, and only for the mages in the group that kills him, and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> if they were currently at that stage of their epic quest.)<br>- Player housing will be available...for a price.<br>- Any class will be able to self-bind.<br>- Tanks will be able to stand beside or in front of casters and absorb attacks even when those attacks are directed towards the casters.<br>- Mobs will accurately con according to the chance of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> one player's</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ability to kill them.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Any</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;green&quot; mob at 50?  You alone will be able to slaughter it.<br>- All players will easily be able to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> solo to lvl 50</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> if they so desire.<br>- Players will be able to &quot;unstick&quot; themselves should they ever get caught in the geography, removing the need to petition for help.<br>- Spells will automatically appear in a caster's spellbook after they level.  No purchase necessary.<br>- Combat skills will be customizable, making a possibility for several different varieties of tanks even if they're the exact same class.<br>- The same holds true for casters and their choices of magic.<br>- Combat and magic skills will be raised using skill points and not through use.<br>- Trade skills will not be dependant on levels, so players will raise one without even taking the other into consideration.<br>- High level players will be able to group with their lower level friends and give up most of their experience so that their low-level friends can gain XP faster and catch up.<br>- Certain buffs that casters will have will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> never run out</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> after being cast unless the caster dies, or casts that particular buff too many times on too many people.<br>- Armor colors will be customizable.  No trade skill needed.<br>- Players will be able to put their wares up for sale without ever having to shout an auction message to the entire zone.<br><br>This is just a small sample of what's to come.<br><br>Oh, did I forget to mention that I'm not talking about EQ?  It'll <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.darkageofcamelot.com">take some homework</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, but you'll figure out what I'm talking about if you don't already. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ualthalustherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Althalus The Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Defender<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#006400>(8/30/01 7:50:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=717.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Features - Coming Soon....</span><hr size=1> /drool <p><I>All assassins had a full-length mirror in their rooms, because it would bea terrible insult to anyone to kill them when you were badly dressed.        -- (Terry Pratchett, Pyramids)</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uexpane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Expane</A><